    • Method Detail

      • push

        void push(E element)
        Adds the element to the top of the Stack, if there is no room, then an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        element - Element to add to the stack

      • pop

        E pop()
        Removes and returns the elements at the top of the Stack. If the stack is empty, then an EmptyStackException will be thrown.
        Returns:
        E Value of the element at the top of the Stack.

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Checks to see if the Stack is empty
        Returns:
        True if the Stack does not contain any elements.

      • size

        int size()
        Returns the number of elements in the stack.
        Returns:
        Number of elements within the stack

      • setCapacity

        void setCapacity(int capacity)
        Set's the capacity of the stack. If the actual parameter is negative or less than the size of the current stack, then an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        capacity - capacity of the stack.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the capacity parameter is given a negative value or attempted to be set to a value less than the current stack size.
